in Room 510 to her test.

785
00:54:42,153 --> 00:54:44,864
Make sure Won-mi has lunch after that.
And you, too, Ms. Jung.

786
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:47,200
What about you?
I know you didn't eat breakfast.

787
00:54:47,284 --> 00:54:48,118
You go ahead.

788
00:54:48,201 --> 00:54:50,870
Let me take care of things.
You should go eat fir--

789
00:54:50,954 --> 00:54:52,622
- Take her to get the tests.
- Ah…

790
00:54:52,706 --> 00:54:54,916
Yes, this is Park Soo-yeon, Unit 53.

791
00:54:55,542 --> 00:54:57,877
Hello, Doctor. Yes.

792
00:54:57,961 --> 00:55:01,172
Mr. Oh Jae-guk is acting out,
asking for cigarettes.

793
00:55:01,256 --> 00:55:02,132
Just a moment.

794
00:55:02,215 --> 00:55:05,468
Call Dr. Kong, and ask Mr. Yoon
to escort him to the seclusion room now.

795
00:55:05,552 --> 00:55:06,386
Yes, ma'am.

796
00:55:06,469 --> 00:55:09,764
Yes, Doctor.
I'll call you back after I check on it.

797
00:55:18,273 --> 00:55:19,316
She is just like me.

798
00:55:28,992 --> 00:55:32,454
Ms. Kwon, your blood pressure
is normal at 110 over 70.

799
00:55:33,121 --> 00:55:35,290
You said you had kids, right?

800
00:55:38,335 --> 00:55:39,961
Oh, I did.

801
00:55:40,045 --> 00:55:42,922
Balancing work
and childcare isn't easy, is it?

802
00:55:46,343 --> 00:55:47,302
Well, no. It isn't.

803
00:55:48,178 --> 00:55:50,764
How old is your daughter, Ms. Kwon?

804
00:55:51,473 --> 00:55:52,599
She's in eighth grade.

805
00:55:53,808 --> 00:55:54,768
Ah.

806
00:55:54,851 --> 00:55:56,811
She must have a lot of studying to do.

807
00:55:57,937 --> 00:56:00,273
May I ask what kind of classes she takes?

808
00:56:01,149 --> 00:56:03,860
Well, it's about the same as other kids.

809
00:56:03,943 --> 00:56:06,446
She has after-school classes
and private lessons.

810
00:56:09,115 --> 00:56:12,827
The tutoring coordinator
you talked about on the phone,

811
00:56:13,536 --> 00:56:15,955
could you introduce me to her too?

812
00:56:16,039 --> 00:56:19,542
Oh, yes. I'll give you her number later.

813
00:56:20,543 --> 00:56:21,795
Thank you.

814
00:56:21,878 --> 00:56:24,631
Back in the day,
I also bent over backward,

815
00:56:24,714 --> 00:56:28,301
currying favor with the moms
in the group chat to get invited.

816
00:56:29,302 --> 00:56:32,472
The moment I got invited,
it felt as though I'd been exonerated.

817
00:56:34,307 --> 00:56:35,725
I hadn't been a bad mom,

818
00:56:36,726 --> 00:56:40,397
but that was the crowning achievement
of my life as a mom for sure.

819
00:56:42,315 --> 00:56:44,067
That thought still stands to this day.

820
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:47,362
That's exactly how I feel right now.

821
00:56:49,697 --> 00:56:52,158
I feel like I'm being a bad mom.

822
00:56:54,702 --> 00:56:56,204
How old are your kids?

823
00:56:57,664 --> 00:56:59,207
I have a third-grader

824
00:57:00,333 --> 00:57:01,668
and a kindergartener.

825
00:57:02,293 --> 00:57:05,255
People not in the know
would see us as overbearing moms,

826
00:57:05,338 --> 00:57:07,006
making a fuss over such little kids.

827
00:57:07,090 --> 00:57:08,550
I work extra hard

828
00:57:08,633 --> 00:57:12,595
to not give anyone an excuse
to blame it on my being a working mom.

829
00:57:13,721 --> 00:57:14,722
But

830
00:57:15,473 --> 00:57:16,307
it's hard.

831
00:57:18,810 --> 00:57:22,105
More than anything, though,
I feel so terrible for my kids.

832
00:57:24,983 --> 00:57:27,485
But it's not like I can quit my job.

833
00:57:28,153 --> 00:57:29,070
If I'm making money…

834
00:57:29,154 --> 00:57:32,907
If I'm making money, I could get her
a better tutor with my income.

835
00:57:33,575 --> 00:57:37,996
I don't want to be short on money
when they really need my support later on.

836
00:57:39,080 --> 00:57:42,000
They say that these days
moms' communities are important.

837
00:57:42,709 --> 00:57:46,421
Working moms have no access
to information and tend to get left out.

838
00:57:46,504 --> 00:57:50,425
And kids can't make friends if their moms
are not a part of those communities.

839
00:57:52,635 --> 00:57:53,678
What if my baby

840
00:57:55,054 --> 00:57:57,432
can't even make friends because of me?

841
00:57:59,517 --> 00:58:01,102
It's all I'm really living for.

842
00:58:01,186 --> 00:58:03,438
Working hard to give my child

843
00:58:04,689 --> 00:58:06,399
a better shot at life.

844
00:58:07,692 --> 00:58:09,152
Don't push yourself so hard.

845
00:58:13,448 --> 00:58:14,616
You will suffer.

846
00:58:17,952 --> 00:58:21,498
Even after you've given them everything,
you'll only beat yourself up

847
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:23,500
over the things you've missed

848
00:58:26,002 --> 00:58:27,837
and blame yourself for everything.

849
00:58:30,089 --> 00:58:31,424
The guilt will eat you up.

850
00:58:34,219 --> 00:58:37,013
You won't even realize
that you're wilting away.

851
00:58:40,058 --> 00:58:43,561
Your life will be covered
in yellow lights.

852
00:58:46,272 --> 00:58:49,567
But you won't even notice
that life is telling you to slow down.

853
00:58:52,445 --> 00:58:54,113
You'll end up turning a blind eye

854
00:58:55,323 --> 00:58:56,574
to your own happiness

855
00:58:58,618 --> 00:59:00,328
for your child's happiness.

856
00:59:09,837 --> 00:59:10,672
But…

857
00:59:12,757 --> 00:59:16,928
how would you make anyone else happy
if you're not happy yourself?

858
00:59:31,985 --> 00:59:34,487
Oh goodness, I'm sorry.

859
00:59:40,368 --> 00:59:41,286
Don't be sorry.

860
00:59:42,453 --> 00:59:43,329
It's fine.

861
00:59:49,335 --> 00:59:51,421
You worked so hard, didn't you?

